The paper discusses the use of neural networks and reinforcement learning to train a model with external memory, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of external interfaces such as memory, databases, and search engines also suggests a potential overlap with natural language processing (cs.CL) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper's focus on algorithmic tasks and the use of a Turing complete model suggests a potential overlap with computational complexity (cs.CC) or computer science theory (cs.IT).
